WEBVTT

06:01.929 --> 06:06.167
<i>The people of the world
are more or less the same.</i>

06:06.200 --> 06:09.837
<i>Though we may come in
different shapes and colors,</i>

06:09.871 --> 06:13.406
<i>we all share
the same inheritance.</i>

06:13.440 --> 06:18.746
<i>And we all have our back
stories, and our secrets.</i>

06:18.779 --> 06:20.882
<i>Like this man, running along</i>

06:20.915 --> 06:23.184
<i>the river Scheldt in Antwerp.</i>

06:23.217 --> 06:28.089
<i>What is he running from?
What is he trying to escape?</i>

06:29.891 --> 06:33.661
<i>Even though evolution
might seem to mature us,</i>

06:33.694 --> 06:35.763
<i>there are still
parts of our brain</i>

06:35.796 --> 06:38.866
<i>that belong to
our reptile ancestors.</i>

06:38.900 --> 06:41.802
<i>Although we've convinced
ourselves that hate,</i>

06:41.836 --> 06:45.706
<i>revenge, and nemesis
belong to the past,</i>

06:45.740 --> 06:50.845
<i>our ancient ancestor's blood
still runs in our veins,</i>

06:50.878 --> 06:54.081
<i>whether we like it or not.</i>

07:17.672 --> 07:19.874
Feels like
a bloody good campaign.

07:19.907 --> 07:21.242
As usual, you'd have to say.

07:21.275 --> 07:23.778
After holiday,
we'll get started on images.

07:23.811 --> 07:25.813
I'll mail over a few suggestions
for photographers.

07:25.846 --> 07:28.783
Excellent. Have a great
holiday, and we'll be in touch.

07:28.816 --> 07:31.118
- Thank you, guys. Thank you.
- Bye-bye.

07:38.092 --> 07:39.994
You're a genius Henry,
you know that?

07:40.027 --> 07:41.595
Well, I don't know about that.

07:41.629 --> 07:43.564
Haven't we already discussed
your raises?

07:46.767 --> 07:48.903
Five more days, guys,
can't wait.

07:48.936 --> 07:50.071
- Until the holidays, you mean?
- Yeah.

07:50.104 --> 07:51.539
John, we're waiting for you.

07:51.572 --> 07:53.808
Damn it.
I love being at work.

07:53.841 --> 07:55.576
Come on.

07:55.609 --> 07:57.578
So what are your plans?

07:57.611 --> 07:58.879
For the holiday?

07:58.913 --> 08:01.215
We've rented a small house
in Cote d'Azur.

08:01.248 --> 08:04.552
We're gonna head down there,
do lots of long walks on the beach,

08:04.585 --> 08:07.221
piles of books, lots of good
food, that sort of thing.

08:07.254 --> 08:10.291
- Sounds decent.
- Well...

08:10.324 --> 08:11.826
In case you wondered,

08:11.859 --> 08:14.095
we'll be damp proofing
the basement.

08:14.128 --> 08:17.631
Consider that when you complain
about sand in your swimming trunks.

08:37.184 --> 08:39.653
- Hi, Henry.
- Hey, Paula.

08:39.687 --> 08:41.055
- Yeah.
- How are you? Paula...

08:41.088 --> 08:42.890
- Polans... Polanski.
- Polanski.

08:42.923 --> 08:45.026
- Yeah, how are you?
- I'm good.

08:45.059 --> 08:47.661
Wow. It's gotta be
ten years since that...

08:47.695 --> 08:50.765
- Uh, almost exactly. Yeah.
- Wow.

08:50.798 --> 08:52.299
Do you live, uh,
here in Maardam?

08:52.333 --> 08:53.701
No, I live in Antwerp now.

08:53.734 --> 08:56.637
I'm just here
on a couple of days work.

08:56.670 --> 08:57.938
Oh.

09:01.776 --> 09:03.744
- So, Film Academy?
- Yeah.

09:03.778 --> 09:05.946
Mainly because I didn't know
what else to do with myself,

09:05.980 --> 09:09.683
but, uh,
I got in for whatever reason.

09:09.717 --> 09:12.319
Well, to make documentaries,
which is what you're doing now, isn't it?

09:12.353 --> 09:14.855
I think I've seen
one of them on ARTE.

09:14.889 --> 09:17.224
- Uh, <i>Roman Beggars.</i>
- <i>Roman,</i> that's it.

09:17.258 --> 09:19.293
- Won an award.
- Did it?

09:19.326 --> 09:20.861
- Yeah.
- Good for you. That's great.

09:20.895 --> 09:22.897
- Thanks. Thanks.
- Well done.

09:22.930 --> 09:25.666
I haven't actually been back
to Kaalbringen since I've...

09:25.699 --> 09:27.868
Well, I stopped being a teacher.
Wasn't really my thing.

09:27.902 --> 09:29.637
- So...
- Yeah, I know.

09:29.670 --> 09:32.106
You work for one of those big,
uh, advertising agencies.

09:32.139 --> 09:33.841
That's... that's right.
How do you...

09:33.874 --> 09:36.243
The reunion.
Oh, you're on the mailing list.

09:36.277 --> 09:40.047
Oh, right. The reunion.
How was that?

09:40.081 --> 09:43.818
Almost everyone
was there except you.

09:44.251 --> 09:45.352
Oh...

09:46.754 --> 09:48.989
All right, yeah.
I don't know why that was.

09:49.023 --> 09:53.160
- I meant to come.
- Yeah. Sure.

09:53.194 --> 09:54.795
Don't worry.
You weren't the only teacher

09:54.829 --> 09:56.864
- that didn't show up.
- Okay, cool.

09:56.897 --> 09:59.100
An actual fact,
I was just a substitute teacher,

09:59.133 --> 10:01.135
not an actual teacher, so...

10:01.168 --> 10:03.237
- Yeah.
- I don't...

10:03.270 --> 10:05.339
This is me.

10:05.372 --> 10:06.974
- Nice seeing you.
- And you.

10:07.007 --> 10:08.642
I'm just staying
at the Metropole, so...

10:08.676 --> 10:09.743
Okay.

10:09.777 --> 10:11.412
You live here in...
in Maardam?

10:11.445 --> 10:12.947
Yeah, in Wassingen.

10:12.980 --> 10:14.281
It's a dreadful, dreadful place.

10:14.315 --> 10:15.749
But I probably have to win
the Academy Award

10:15.783 --> 10:17.318
to get some advantage, though.

10:17.351 --> 10:19.420
- Anyway...
- Well, listen, it's been nice seeing you.

10:19.453 --> 10:21.021
- Yeah, you, too.
- Bye.

10:21.055 --> 10:22.289
Bye.

10:32.466 --> 10:36.003
<i>Yeah, mainly because I didn't
know what else to do with myself,</i>

10:36.036 --> 10:40.007
<i>but, uh, I got in
for whatever reason.</i>

10:40.040 --> 10:43.878
<i>Well, to make documentaries,
which is what you're doing now, isn't it?</i>

10:55.456 --> 10:58.259
As far as I know,
he's never had a visitor.

10:58.292 --> 11:00.661
You're the first.

11:01.295 --> 11:02.796
What's this for?

11:02.830 --> 11:04.732
It's a... it's a hard drive,

11:04.765 --> 11:06.433
just to store the footage.

11:07.334 --> 11:09.303
Oh, yeah. Hm...

11:09.336 --> 11:10.905
It's all beyond me, any who.

11:15.176 --> 11:19.480
If you ask me,
Jacob Kall is a sick bastard.

11:19.514 --> 11:22.983
He's been in here ten years.
He'll end his days in here.

11:23.784 --> 11:25.719
He'll never be released.

11:29.390 --> 11:30.991
It's a battery.

11:32.326 --> 11:34.061
All right.

11:34.094 --> 11:35.996
Yeah, I'll be
outside that door.

11:36.030 --> 11:38.465
For your sake,
just so you know.

11:38.499 --> 11:41.869
He sometimes gets it
into this head to be violent.

11:41.902 --> 11:43.737
Yeah, yeah, I know.

11:57.985 --> 11:59.787
<i>We never met, you and I,</i>

11:59.820 --> 12:04.191
<i>but I was in the same class
as your daughter, Vera.</i>

12:04.225 --> 12:10.130
<i>You know, she never talked about you
or her life on the farm in Samaria.</i>

12:10.164 --> 12:14.134
<i>Always cycled home
when we went out drinking.</i>

12:14.168 --> 12:16.036
<i>We never really understood why.</i>

12:16.070 --> 12:17.938
<i>Well, she never
talked about it,</i>

12:17.972 --> 12:24.845
<i>but, um, she was so...
important to me.</i>

12:24.878 --> 12:27.948
<i>Well, not just to me,
to all of us.</i>

12:27.982 --> 12:31.553
<i>We had a reunion
a couple of weeks ago.</i>

12:31.586 --> 12:34.088
<i>Almost everyone was there.</i>

12:34.121 --> 12:38.392
<i>And it was really hard</i>

12:38.425 --> 12:40.528
<i>to avoid talking about her.</i>

12:41.996 --> 12:45.833
<i>Your daughter...
your only daughter, even.</i>

12:47.401 --> 12:51.138
<i>Could you tell me a bit about
your relationship with her?</i>

12:51.171 --> 12:52.973
<i>What was she like as a kid?</i>

12:53.007 --> 12:57.177
Was she... happy?

13:03.450 --> 13:05.219
At the reunion,
we talked a lot about

13:05.252 --> 13:07.388
how me missed having
a grave to visit,

13:07.421 --> 13:10.891
and how you're probably the only
person who knows where she's buried.

13:10.924 --> 13:14.562
That's if you even bothered
to bury her?

13:15.462 --> 13:18.299
Only God
knows where Vera is.

13:18.332 --> 13:21.536
Can I ask you
what you believe?

13:21.569 --> 13:24.471
I believe in God
and His will.

13:25.406 --> 13:27.074
Okay.

13:28.909 --> 13:30.177
I don't understand.

13:30.210 --> 13:32.580
Are you saying that Vera's death
was God's will?

13:44.892 --> 13:46.360
Even though you
never made a confession,

13:46.393 --> 13:49.330
and her body was never found,

13:49.363 --> 13:52.966
you were found guilty
and banged up for life.

13:53.000 --> 13:55.102
Do you maintain your innocence?

14:00.040 --> 14:02.209
Do you also claim to be
innocent of the accusations

14:02.242 --> 14:05.513
that you repeatedly
mistreated her as a child?

14:05.547 --> 14:08.616
Injuries that were documented
by the school nurse.

14:08.650 --> 14:11.018
The accident and emergency
department at Kaalbringen.

14:11.051 --> 14:13.320
Although neither Vera
nor your wife

14:13.354 --> 14:15.356
dared to speak out about it.

14:17.124 --> 14:21.462
Paula, I think you're
looking for some sort of guilt.

14:23.665 --> 14:27.334
The guilt laid on my shoulders
is of this world.

14:28.268 --> 14:30.371
But I'll tell you what,

14:30.404 --> 14:33.107
this world doesn't belong to me.

14:34.942 --> 14:38.479
What human being has the right
to kill another person?

14:40.047 --> 14:44.351
We are all just
simple instruments

14:44.385 --> 14:45.953
of a greater will.

14:45.986 --> 14:48.222
So you claim your innocence.

14:48.255 --> 14:49.890
So who did kill her?

14:55.062 --> 14:56.531
I sit here...

14:57.965 --> 15:01.001
most likely knocked up
for the rest of my life.

15:01.034 --> 15:03.303
And it was
probably meant to be.

15:04.071 --> 15:05.607
Sorry.

15:06.641 --> 15:08.909
It's meant to be.

15:12.312 --> 15:15.650
You see, I can get
so much more work done in here.

15:15.683 --> 15:19.453
There are people in here
who are willing to listen.

15:22.624 --> 15:27.695
So many lost souls
finally have a safe haven.

15:38.673 --> 15:41.676
The question is rather if you,

15:41.709 --> 15:44.512
Paula Polanski,
can understand this.

15:54.756 --> 15:57.559
I've been thinking about
where you must have buried her.

15:57.592 --> 16:00.194
I know the police did some
digging and searched with dogs.

16:00.227 --> 16:03.096
But down by the river,
there's this little piece of land.

16:03.130 --> 16:05.700
And I'm thinking maybe that's
where they should have looked?

16:06.501 --> 16:08.770
Or on the other side?

16:08.803 --> 16:11.472
In the forest? Yeah?

16:13.373 --> 16:15.610
I'm thinking
she must have been heavy.

16:15.643 --> 16:18.345
Dead body weighs a ton.

16:18.378 --> 16:19.581
Maybe you used your tractor?

16:19.614 --> 16:21.415
Though you
would've had to dug deep

16:21.448 --> 16:24.251
because you wouldn't want
a fox to dig her up.

16:27.488 --> 16:31.526
I've never quite grasped
why all you little people

16:31.559 --> 16:35.496
need to know everything.

16:35.530 --> 16:40.300
It's a human weakness
to be obsessed with the truth.

16:40.334 --> 16:42.202
As if it were up to us.

16:42.236 --> 16:46.674
As if the truth even existed.

17:14.368 --> 17:16.236
Already done?

17:16.270 --> 17:19.306
Yeah.
Didn't get very far.

17:19.339 --> 17:23.110
Right.
Let's get going, Jacob.

17:25.379 --> 17:27.447
I'll just take him
through the security gate.

17:27.481 --> 17:30.450
If you wait here,
I'll see you out after that.

17:30.484 --> 17:31.653
Thanks.

17:31.686 --> 17:34.221
That question you never asked.

17:35.557 --> 17:39.159
No, I didn't kill Vera.

17:51.338 --> 17:52.607
Yeah, I've just finished.

17:52.640 --> 17:55.242
Just... just on my way
to that meeting.

17:56.376 --> 17:58.846
Yeah, I know, I just wanna...

17:58.880 --> 18:01.649
I promise.
Just... I hear you.

18:01.683 --> 18:03.216
I promise I will.

18:05.152 --> 18:07.755
I'll probably be on
the 7:00 train anyways.

18:07.789 --> 18:10.558
No, don't be silly.
I'll just get a taxi.

18:11.458 --> 18:13.260
All right.
I love you.

18:24.304 --> 18:26.908
It was the first time we'd all
been together since then.

18:26.941 --> 18:29.376
So... but it...

18:29.409 --> 18:33.781
It was like everyone
needed to talk about Vera.

18:33.815 --> 18:36.684
Felt unfinished... somehow.

18:37.785 --> 18:41.689
I mean, really, we...

18:41.723 --> 18:44.826
Could have done
with a grave visit.

18:44.859 --> 18:46.694
It was a strange time.
It was...

18:46.728 --> 18:50.230
Life got too serious
much too soon, it felt.

18:50.263 --> 18:51.498
More so for you than for me.

18:51.532 --> 18:53.166
Yeah. Yeah.

18:53.200 --> 18:54.936
Sorry.
Uh, care for another?

18:54.969 --> 18:57.605
Um, yeah.
Yeah, thanks.

18:57.639 --> 18:59.507
- Not for me. Thank you.
- Oh.

19:00.642 --> 19:02.309
So...

19:02.644 --> 19:03.778
Hm?

19:03.811 --> 19:05.445
Apart from that,
what's happening?

19:05.479 --> 19:06.413
Shacked up?

19:06.446 --> 19:07.882
Married? No.

19:07.915 --> 19:11.418
I'm living with someone.
Clara, in Antwerp.

19:11.451 --> 19:13.220
She's... she's great.

19:13.588 --> 19:14.656
Ooh.

19:17.290 --> 19:18.860
Found these the other day.

19:18.893 --> 19:21.428
Oh, no.

19:22.797 --> 19:24.464
Ring any bells?

19:24.498 --> 19:26.400
Dear, oh, dear.

19:27.434 --> 19:28.836
Where have you got this?

19:28.870 --> 19:31.572
That's a long time ago.
I remember that.

19:33.007 --> 19:36.978
Oh, this is the, uh,
the graduation party at, uh, the, um...

19:37.011 --> 19:40.380
- Limburg Rooms.
- The Limburg Rooms, that's right.

19:40.414 --> 19:42.617
Goodness me. You were
walking around that night

19:42.650 --> 19:44.585
with your fantastic
old camera, as always.

19:44.619 --> 19:45.787
Yeah. Nikon.

19:45.820 --> 19:46.821
- All right.
- Oh, thank you.

19:49.256 --> 19:50.758
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

19:50.792 --> 19:53.393
- I used to develop my own pictures as well.
- Right.

19:53.427 --> 19:56.864
Was the worst kind of nerd,
even then.

19:56.898 --> 19:59.834
Here you are.
Schoolmaster Maertens.

19:59.867 --> 20:03.571
A tie? What on Earth
was I thinking?

20:03.604 --> 20:07.274
Here's me with, um,
with Sebastian.

20:07.307 --> 20:09.911
Oh, look at that.
You haven't changed, have you?

20:09.944 --> 20:11.713
Oh, thanks.

20:13.380 --> 20:16.584
And here she is,
Vera Kall.

20:20.922 --> 20:22.289
Oh.

20:41.809 --> 20:43.511
What was her father called?

20:43.544 --> 20:44.912
- Jacob.
- Jacob.

20:44.946 --> 20:48.683
- He's locked up in Bittinger.
- Yeah.

20:48.716 --> 20:50.685
Serving life sentence.

20:50.718 --> 20:52.887
Maintains his innocence.

20:52.920 --> 20:54.789
Actually, I met him yesterday.

20:54.822 --> 20:56.423
Met him?
That Jacob Kall?

20:56.456 --> 20:58.993
Yeah.
I... I interviewed him.

21:02.530 --> 21:04.464
I'm gonna make a film.

21:05.499 --> 21:09.436
Tell the story...
story of Vera.

21:09.469 --> 21:10.872
I think she's worth that much.

21:17.612 --> 21:19.547
I'd really like you
to be in it.

21:31.692 --> 21:34.061
- Henry...
- I was a substitute teacher

21:34.095 --> 21:35.830
for one term, all right?
I have to get my train.

21:35.863 --> 21:37.865
But you were an important person
to all of us.

21:37.899 --> 21:40.367
And the film
is not gonna be about you.

21:40.400 --> 21:41.969
I've already spoken
to Beatrice Motte,

21:42.003 --> 21:43.504
I'm gonna speak to
Commissioner Keller,

21:43.538 --> 21:45.506
and I'll speak to Jacob Kall
again if I have to.

21:45.540 --> 21:48.408
Although, I'd... I'd...
I'd rather not.

21:48.441 --> 21:50.878
A girl in your class
was murdered.

21:50.912 --> 21:52.680
I'm really surprised
you don't seem to care.

21:52.713 --> 21:54.048
I don't wanna be in your film.
I'm sorry.

21:54.081 --> 21:55.583
What, because you think
it's a bad idea?

21:58.586 --> 22:00.621
It will open up
a lot of old wounds,

22:00.655 --> 22:02.790
and it will upset
a lot of people.

22:02.824 --> 22:04.025
I do believe that.

22:04.058 --> 22:06.093
I think it's better
to just let things lie.

22:06.127 --> 22:08.129
Okay. I know that.

22:08.162 --> 22:09.764
- Good.
- But...

22:11.799 --> 22:13.734
I am gonna make this film.

22:15.670 --> 22:18.105
You'll have to do it without me.
I'm sorry.

24:43.818 --> 24:45.987
Yes, I rented out
the upper floor

24:46.020 --> 24:47.655
because it was rather difficult

24:47.688 --> 24:51.525
managing my own finances
after my husband passed away.

24:51.559 --> 24:53.060
God bless him.

24:53.094 --> 24:55.196
He was useless in most ways,

24:55.229 --> 24:57.531
but there were certain things

24:57.565 --> 24:59.233
I'd still come to depend
on him for.

24:59.266 --> 25:01.535
Sorry.

25:03.871 --> 25:09.310
Um... I'm gonna take this,
actually. Sorry.

25:09.343 --> 25:10.945
- Hello.
- <i>Paula.</i>

25:10.978 --> 25:12.580
Hi. It's... it's Henry Maertens.

25:12.613 --> 25:13.581
Am I calling at a bad time?

25:13.614 --> 25:15.149
No, no, no, no.
Not at all.

25:15.182 --> 25:17.018
<i>Great. I... I was thinking
maybe I'll take</i>

25:17.051 --> 25:18.652
a trip to Kaalbringen
after all.

25:18.686 --> 25:20.321
- <i>Yeah?</i>
- Yes, well, I was thinking

25:20.354 --> 25:21.756
about what you said.

25:21.789 --> 25:24.992
And, uh, maybe I could
be of some help.

25:25.026 --> 25:26.694
Great.

25:26.727 --> 25:28.662
Is the Hotel Continental
still there, do you know?

25:28.696 --> 25:34.568
Uh... uh, I think so, but, um,
you could stay with me.

25:34.602 --> 25:37.271
I've, I've borrowed my parents'
summerhouse by the river.

25:37.304 --> 25:39.206
No, no, I don't... I, um...

25:39.240 --> 25:40.641
<i>There's plenty of space.</i>

25:40.674 --> 25:42.343
And you can tell Clara
that I'm gay,

25:42.376 --> 25:44.812
so... so no problem there.

25:44.845 --> 25:47.681
- Um...
- <i>Let's just leave it at that.</i>

25:47.715 --> 25:49.316
Let me find The Continental,
see if they have a room.

25:49.350 --> 25:51.252
Ah, okay, I'm just about
to drive through a tunnel.

25:52.386 --> 25:54.155
Pau...

25:56.724 --> 25:58.993
Sorry.

25:59.026 --> 26:01.729
Okay.
Uh, where were we?

26:01.762 --> 26:08.135
Um, were there lots of, uh,
visitors or friends dropping in?

26:08.169 --> 26:11.272
<i>Well, I don't know.
I... I can't really remember.</i>

26:11.305 --> 26:13.808
<i>It was a long time ago.</i>

26:28.389 --> 26:31.292
<i>Wow. It's gotta be
ten years since then.</i>

26:31.325 --> 26:33.794
- <i>Almost exactly.</i>
- <i>An actual fact,</i>

26:33.828 --> 26:36.263
<i>I was just a substitute
teacher, not an actual teacher.</i>

26:36.297 --> 26:38.232
<i>Yeah, I know.</i>

26:45.172 --> 26:48.209
Hi. I'm looking for Mr. Kruggel.

26:48.242 --> 26:50.344
I'm Henry Maertens,
the substitute teacher.

26:50.377 --> 26:51.846
Oh. I'm Susanne.

26:51.879 --> 26:53.414
Come in.
Dad's waiting for you.

26:53.447 --> 26:54.648
Thanks.

26:56.150 --> 26:58.385
Can't imagine
he'll ever improve.

26:58.419 --> 27:00.855
Always late.
Always.

27:00.888 --> 27:06.293
Uh, Emil Bachmann.
An idiot.

27:09.430 --> 27:11.832
Okay. Uh, Paula Polanski.

27:11.866 --> 27:14.902
She did very well in her,
uh, in her standard test.

27:14.935 --> 27:17.438
- Paula Polanski?
- I don't know, I...

27:17.471 --> 27:19.440
I haven't actually met
any of the students yet.

27:19.473 --> 27:24.311
Ah, the mousey one. Yes.

27:30.384 --> 27:32.186
We're nearly finished.
I promise.

27:32.219 --> 27:35.923
Um, Niels Buhltoft?

27:35.956 --> 27:38.859
Uh, neither fish nor fowl.

27:38.893 --> 27:42.029
Uh, unless he does something
out of the ordinary

27:42.062 --> 27:46.133
in his special assignment
on literature.

27:46.167 --> 27:48.836
Um, can I offer you
a coffee or something?

27:50.037 --> 27:53.207
Um... no, do you know what?
I think I'm good.

27:53.240 --> 27:55.709
- I think I should probably go.
- Okay.

27:55.743 --> 27:57.845
Thanks so much for your help.
I, uh, I have an appointment

27:57.878 --> 28:00.347
with the, uh, the headmaster
in 20 minutes. So...

28:29.544 --> 28:31.278
- <i>Hey.</i>
- <i>Hi.</i>

28:31.312 --> 28:34.014
- You all right?
- Yeah, good. Welcome.

28:34.048 --> 28:35.115
Thank you.

28:36.450 --> 28:39.353
- Good to see you.
- Yeah, yeah, you too.

28:42.389 --> 28:44.491
I... I was surprised
when you called

28:44.526 --> 28:47.328
because when we met in Maardam,
you sounded...

28:47.361 --> 28:49.063
- Yeah.
- Very negative.

28:49.096 --> 28:50.831
Yeah, sorry, about that.

28:52.534 --> 28:55.102
Yeah, I managed to get
a couple of days free.

28:55.135 --> 28:57.838
Clara's, uh,
she'd step into work this week.

28:57.871 --> 29:01.041
She's a doctor, yup.
Cardiologist.

29:09.850 --> 29:12.419
Did... did I tell you
about Vera's mother?

29:12.453 --> 29:14.154
No.

29:14.188 --> 29:17.291
Well, she... she died
a couple of months ago.

29:17.324 --> 29:18.792
Oh.

29:18.826 --> 29:22.329
When Vera's father
was convicted, she left.

29:22.363 --> 29:26.934
She just walked out
of that house, never went back.

29:26.967 --> 29:29.470
Moved in with
her sister, apparently.

29:30.204 --> 29:31.438
Mm...

29:42.983 --> 29:45.953
- Samaria.
- What?

29:45.986 --> 29:49.023
It's the name of the farm
where Vera grew up.

29:49.056 --> 29:50.558
Ah, yeah.

29:50.592 --> 29:53.160
Sounds so beautiful.

29:53.193 --> 29:55.029
Samaria? Yeah.

29:56.430 --> 29:58.999
Yeah, I suppose it does.

29:59.033 --> 30:03.304
Like something out of
a fairytale... almost.

30:04.872 --> 30:09.310
- A little like Vera herself.
- Hm, yeah, maybe.

30:34.034 --> 30:35.503
Bit hungover today, guys?

30:36.671 --> 30:38.640
No pleasure without pain,
isn't it?

30:38.673 --> 30:40.074
All right?

30:40.107 --> 30:41.975
You don't know
what's happened, do you?

30:42.009 --> 30:43.310
What?

30:43.344 --> 30:47.414
Vera. Vera Kall.
She never came home last night.

30:47.448 --> 30:51.218
- Oh.
- Her mother report her missing to the police.

30:52.986 --> 30:54.622
Well, I'm sure she's fine.
I'm sure she probably

30:54.656 --> 30:57.024
just stayed over
with a friend or something.

30:58.058 --> 31:00.427
Okay? She'll be fine.

31:05.165 --> 31:07.067
- Hey.
- Hey.

31:07.101 --> 31:08.435
Can I get a double espresso,
please?

31:08.469 --> 31:10.505
Of course. Coming up.

31:14.308 --> 31:17.177
<i>This is not only about
Vera and her family,</i>

31:17.211 --> 31:21.215
it is about all of us
at City College.

31:21.248 --> 31:23.484
So I'd like to remind you
that all information,

31:23.518 --> 31:28.489
anything you saw at the Limburg
Rooms could be vitally important.

31:29.591 --> 31:31.125
You may think some item
of information

31:31.158 --> 31:33.927
is of no use at all,
but it could prove to be

31:33.961 --> 31:36.363
exactly that little
missing piece of the puzzle,

31:36.397 --> 31:39.567
that will bring clarity to the circumstances
surrounding Vera's disappearance.

31:39.601 --> 31:43.137
So don't hesitate.

31:44.506 --> 31:46.641
If for some reason
you don't want to talk

31:46.674 --> 31:50.645
to the police directly,
we are here.

31:50.678 --> 31:53.515
You can turn
to any member of staff.

31:54.381 --> 31:57.251
Or to me, of course.

32:16.538 --> 32:17.705
Wow.

32:20.274 --> 32:21.576
It's great.

32:21.609 --> 32:24.712
Yeah.
Yeah, it's nice, isn't it?

32:26.013 --> 32:28.015
So I've, um,
I've given you the room

32:28.048 --> 32:30.984
- that overlooks the river.
- Okay. Sounds very flash.

32:31.018 --> 32:33.588
And I've, uh, I've moved myself
into the box room.

32:33.621 --> 32:35.757
Ah.

32:35.790 --> 32:37.525
So how long can you stay?

32:37.559 --> 32:39.493
Couple of days, if not, more.

32:40.127 --> 32:41.663
Cool.

33:13.126 --> 33:15.663
How are you planning on
making this film?

33:15.697 --> 33:17.799
Well, when you're
making a documentary,

33:17.832 --> 33:19.767
you don't really know
where it's gonna end,

33:19.801 --> 33:24.271
but I'm trying to meet everyone
who knew her, interview them,

33:24.304 --> 33:27.374
and see if I can build up
a picture of her.

33:27.407 --> 33:29.409
With all the plans
to visit the grave,

33:29.443 --> 33:31.245
or whatever it is
we're calling it?

33:31.278 --> 33:32.814
Yeah, that might
have been part of my plan,

33:32.847 --> 33:34.481
but having met Jacob Kall,

33:34.516 --> 33:36.651
I'd say that's a little
too much to hope for.

33:37.752 --> 33:40.053
Going for a new angle?

33:40.087 --> 33:42.524
Um, remains to be seen.

33:42.557 --> 33:47.695
You know, she...
she clearly made an impression.

33:47.729 --> 33:50.364
Everybody has
their own picture of Vera.

33:50.397 --> 33:54.101
I know I do, anyway.
Maybe you do as well.

33:54.134 --> 33:56.169
Uh, yeah, as I recall her,
she was a very good student.

33:56.203 --> 33:59.541
I want to understand,
partially just who she was,

33:59.574 --> 34:02.744
but also what it does to us when
someone just disappears out of our...

34:02.777 --> 34:07.515
You know, how we just carry on
living as if nothing has happened.

34:07.549 --> 34:09.449
And is that what we really do?

34:09.483 --> 34:11.418
I suppose not.

34:12.620 --> 34:13.821
Do you want coffee?

34:13.855 --> 34:17.257
Please. Yeah, that'd be great.
Thanks.

34:17.291 --> 34:20.093
At the same time, there is some
strange stuff in this story.

34:20.127 --> 34:23.831
For instance, why did it take the
police so long to arrest her father?

34:23.865 --> 34:26.133
And what was her mother's role
in all of this?

34:26.166 --> 34:28.803
Is she completely exonerated?

34:28.836 --> 34:33.340
Or what if Jacob Kall is telling
the truth and he's innocent?

34:35.208 --> 34:36.778
Are you serious?

34:38.580 --> 34:40.247
No, no, no, he's a monster,

34:40.280 --> 34:42.884
I mean, you just have to
keep the door open

34:42.917 --> 34:45.118
- when it's a work in progress.
- Of course.

34:45.152 --> 34:46.453
I'm guessing
you know how to do that.

34:46.486 --> 34:48.590
I hope so.

34:59.366 --> 35:00.735
It was just like
in that film

35:00.768 --> 35:02.402
with, um, Bill Murray.

35:02.436 --> 35:04.471
What's it called?
Uh, <i>Groundhog Day.</i>

35:04.505 --> 35:09.577
<i>I rented a room from an old
widow, uh, Mrs. Kuntze.</i>

35:14.549 --> 35:17.685
<i>Same routine, every morning.</i>

35:17.719 --> 35:19.887
<i>It was me and this guy,
Kellerman,</i>

35:19.921 --> 35:22.189
<i>an optician's assistant.
Aged...</i>

35:22.222 --> 35:25.526
- Morning, Kellerman.
- <i>...somewhere between 30 and 60.</i>

35:25.560 --> 35:31.599
<i>We shared a bathroom with, uh, Tomas, Mrs.
Kuntze's old cat.</i>

35:32.466 --> 35:33.735
I don't think he ever said

35:33.768 --> 35:35.503
one word to me
while I was there.

35:35.536 --> 35:37.839
Who? The cat or Kellerman?

35:37.872 --> 35:39.473
Very good.

35:47.515 --> 35:48.716
No, thanks.

35:48.750 --> 35:52.252
I, um... packed those in
a long time ago.

35:54.287 --> 35:59.493
So tell me about...
uh, about Clara.

36:00.795 --> 36:02.496
Yeah, what...
what do you wanna know?

36:02.530 --> 36:04.297
- You live in Antwerp.
- Mm-hm.

36:04.331 --> 36:07.502
- She's a... a doctor.
- Doctor. Yeah.

36:07.535 --> 36:09.671
- You're a copywriter.
- Mm-hm.

36:09.704 --> 36:12.205
What else? Any, any kids?

36:12.239 --> 36:14.174
No. No.

36:15.308 --> 36:16.644
We, um...

36:18.846 --> 36:20.748
Didn't, uh...

36:22.550 --> 36:24.619
Hasn't really worked out.

36:24.652 --> 36:26.688
That kinda thing.

36:26.721 --> 36:31.324
If, um... Yeah.

36:59.352 --> 37:00.922
Was... was it something I said?

37:00.955 --> 37:03.691
Oh, no. Don't be silly.
No, um, things have been

37:03.725 --> 37:07.294
very hard on the home front
of late but...

37:09.362 --> 37:13.501
- You wanna talk about it?
- There's not a lot to say.

37:13.534 --> 37:15.302
Clara and I always
intended to have children,

37:15.335 --> 37:18.039
but I've later backed away from
it, I don't know why.

37:18.072 --> 37:21.042
So on Tuesday, she decided
she'd waited long enough.

37:21.075 --> 37:23.678
She took the car and the dog
and went to her sister's house.

37:23.711 --> 37:25.412
Cancelled the reservation
for the house

37:25.445 --> 37:26.948
that we're about to rent
in the south of France,

37:26.981 --> 37:29.984
- and doesn't answer my calls.
- So that's why you came.

37:30.017 --> 37:31.485
No.

37:33.888 --> 37:35.388
How about you?
Anyone?

37:35.422 --> 37:38.659
Um... Oh...

37:40.327 --> 37:44.498
I... I don't know,
I've, um...

37:44.532 --> 37:46.868
- Taking some time out from that sorta thing.
- Right.

37:46.901 --> 37:51.038
I'm not so good at the whole
relationship, uh, thing, yeah.

37:52.874 --> 37:55.977
- Thank you.
- She just, um...

37:56.010 --> 37:58.579
She started seeing
somebody else.

37:58.613 --> 38:02.517
And everything just
ran into the sand.

38:02.550 --> 38:04.417
I don't know.

38:07.420 --> 38:09.356
Maybe it s just as well.

38:09.991 --> 38:11.324
Yeah.

38:17.131 --> 38:20.635
So, uh, what do you
remember about us?

38:22.103 --> 38:24.371
Us, your students...

38:24.404 --> 38:26.473
- Oh.
- In class 3B at City College?

38:28.810 --> 38:30.077
<i>I liked being your teacher.</i>

38:30.111 --> 38:31.646
<i>I liked it.</i>

38:34.749 --> 38:36.584
<i>Not everyone, of course.</i>

38:36.617 --> 38:39.486
<i>You know, some I like less,
like, a lot less.</i>

38:41.622 --> 38:45.092
<i>But, you know, others more.</i>

38:50.164 --> 38:53.935
<i>It felt strange at times being
in a position of authority</i>

38:53.968 --> 38:56.804
<i>when I was only
a few years older than you.</i>

38:59.073 --> 39:01.008
Don't forget
tomorrow's the deadline

39:01.042 --> 39:02.510
for handing in
your poetry analysis.

39:02.543 --> 39:03.978
Do not forget, please.

39:04.011 --> 39:05.613
<i>But then that's how it was.</i>

39:05.646 --> 39:08.015
<i>I was your teacher
and you were my student.</i>

39:08.049 --> 39:09.416
Good.

39:21.662 --> 39:23.898
<i>Every day, I'd pack up,</i>

39:23.931 --> 39:27.400
<i>and then home again to...
to Mrs. Kuntze.</i>

39:29.503 --> 39:32.506
<i>And we lived in a beautiful
neighborhood called the Pampa...</i>

39:32.540 --> 39:33.741
<i>well, the Pampas, you know.</i>

39:33.774 --> 39:35.943
- Hi. How are you?
- Nothing for you.

39:35.977 --> 39:37.444
Oh. Every time.

39:37.477 --> 39:39.412
<i>I came and went
as I pleased, really.</i>

39:39.446 --> 39:41.883
- What have you been doing today?
- Today was good.

39:41.916 --> 39:44.185
Today, uh, I have 30 students
doing an essay

39:44.218 --> 39:45.887
- on narrative structure.
- Oh, dear.

39:45.920 --> 39:47.454
- Yes.
- Narrative...

39:47.487 --> 39:49.190
<i>And Mrs. Kuntze,
she was very kind.</i>

39:49.223 --> 39:51.559
<i>As was her cat, Tomas.</i>

39:54.695 --> 39:58.799
<i>And then every night
I'd sit up, correct tests,</i>

39:58.833 --> 40:03.905
<i>prepare my work,
eventually falling asleep,</i>

40:03.938 --> 40:06.941
<i>and waking again
to another exciting day.</i>

41:13.140 --> 41:15.643
<i>When we got
changed after gym class,</i>

41:15.676 --> 41:17.645
<i>I noticed she had
a big bruise on her arm.</i>

41:17.678 --> 41:19.914
<i>She said she'd hurt herself
on some gym equipment.</i>

41:19.947 --> 41:23.050
- <i>Oh, my God.</i>
- <i>I didn't know how things were for her at home.</i>

41:23.084 --> 41:25.686
- <i>She never opened up about it.</i>
- <i>She didn't with anyone.</i>

41:25.720 --> 41:27.955
<i>I mean, she could have
moved in with me!</i>

41:30.624 --> 41:32.126
<i>I should have done something.</i>

41:32.159 --> 41:34.061
<i>It was before it was too late.</i>

41:34.095 --> 41:36.163
<i>That... that was...</i>

41:36.197 --> 41:40.735
<i>I don't think there's anything any
of us could have done, you know?</i>

41:46.107 --> 41:49.143
<i>I remember that party
as if it were yesterday,</i>

41:50.211 --> 41:52.046
<i>the one at the Limburg Rooms.</i>

41:53.047 --> 41:54.281
<i>When are you thinking?</i>

41:56.584 --> 41:58.819
<i>It was the last time
I spoke to her,</i>

41:58.853 --> 42:00.321
<i>in the girls' loo.</i>

42:00.354 --> 42:02.823
<i>What time was that?</i>

42:02.857 --> 42:05.793
<i>Eleven? Half past.</i>

42:05.826 --> 42:07.695
<i>And anything else?</i>

42:09.897 --> 42:11.999
<i>I don't know.</i>

42:12.033 --> 42:14.802
<i>It's just...
the whole thing's so sad.</i>

42:14.835 --> 42:17.271
- <i>Yeah.</i>
- <i>She was so happy!</i>

42:17.304 --> 42:18.739
<i>Happy?</i>

42:18.773 --> 42:20.074
<i>She wasn't usually the sort</i>

42:20.107 --> 42:23.044
- <i>to be cheerful exactly.</i>
- <i>No.</i>

42:23.077 --> 42:26.680
<i>It was as if something
good had happened in her life.</i>

42:30.885 --> 42:33.187
Anyway, that's all I got
because her kid

42:33.220 --> 42:36.023
hit his head and started
screaming and, you know.

42:36.057 --> 42:38.659
Great not to have kids.

42:40.861 --> 42:44.732
- Sorry, sorry.
- I'm gonna go for a dip.

42:44.765 --> 42:48.035
- I think I need to cool down a bit.
- Okay.

42:48.069 --> 42:50.738
Hey, uh, you know,
Commissioner Keller

42:50.771 --> 42:53.207
is coming in an hour,
if you wanna join.

42:53.240 --> 42:56.911
Um... maybe I could
borrow the car?

42:58.145 --> 42:59.246
- Okay.
- Great!

42:59.280 --> 43:02.383
Um, but, uh,
my dad will kill you

43:02.416 --> 43:04.018
if anything happens to that car,
you know.

43:04.051 --> 43:06.720
No, no, no, I'm...
I'm serious, not a scratch.

43:35.783 --> 43:37.718
<i>Nah, school's
closed, it's summer.</i>

43:37.751 --> 43:41.122
I know that. I know.
I, um, I used to work here.

43:41.155 --> 43:43.724
I was just wondering if I could
have a quick look around.

43:45.392 --> 43:47.161
Let me know when you leave.

43:47.194 --> 43:48.629
Thank you.

44:28.302 --> 44:29.770
Yeah.

44:32.306 --> 44:33.374
Can I come in?

44:33.407 --> 44:35.342
Of course, you can, yeah.

44:38.045 --> 44:39.847
Do with your help.

44:39.880 --> 44:41.916
All right. Okay.

44:47.755 --> 44:49.356
What can I help with?

44:49.390 --> 44:52.126
I can't make up my mind
which one to choose?

44:52.527 --> 44:54.695
Okay.

44:55.095 --> 44:56.297
Ah...

44:57.965 --> 45:00.334
<i>Journey to the End of the Night</i>
and <i>Madame Bovary.</i>

45:00.367 --> 45:02.736
Well, you've chosen
two entirely different texts,

45:02.770 --> 45:04.905
both classics.

45:04.939 --> 45:09.376
Um, this is one of the world's
best known love stories.

45:11.312 --> 45:13.347
Really, I'd like
to write about both,

45:13.380 --> 45:16.750
but that might seem
a bit overambitious.

45:16.784 --> 45:18.152
Yeah, maybe a little bit.

45:18.185 --> 45:21.422
Um, Céline, on the other hand...

45:25.426 --> 45:30.130
Uh, well, this is very dark.

45:31.465 --> 45:34.401
It's all about the First World
War, a lot of anguish.

45:34.435 --> 45:37.104
He was almost obsessed by death,
wasn't he?

45:37.137 --> 45:40.107
Oh, that's a little bit
of an understatement, but, yeah.

45:43.911 --> 45:47.815
I don't know.
I suppose if one...

45:47.848 --> 45:50.284
if one were to say that Céline
is the true pessimist,

45:50.317 --> 45:53.254
then you could also say that
Flaubert is his complete opposite.

45:53.287 --> 45:56.257
If I were you,
I'd go for the Flaubert.

45:56.290 --> 45:59.260
- Hmm.
- Because life is gloomy enough even without Céline in it.

45:59.293 --> 46:03.397
And a little bit of love,
never did anybody any harm, so...

46:04.932 --> 46:07.935
- Thanks.
- You're very welcome.

46:11.506 --> 46:13.575
Then I know.

46:13.608 --> 46:15.142
You've decided?

46:15.175 --> 46:16.511
Yeah.

46:17.411 --> 46:19.046
This one, of course.

46:24.451 --> 46:25.919
Thanks.

46:31.392 --> 46:33.027
<i>In the beginning
she was just missing,</i>

46:33.060 --> 46:34.895
<i>so we waited for her to return,</i>

46:34.928 --> 46:37.464
but she never did, in the end.

46:37.498 --> 46:40.134
So we dredged the river,

46:40.167 --> 46:45.105
searched her cycle routes
with dogs, formed human chains.

46:45.139 --> 46:48.142
I think we questioned
close to 150 people.

46:48.175 --> 46:51.145
Wow. You had a few
other suspects, didn't you?

46:51.178 --> 46:52.846
Before you detained
Jacob Kall?

46:52.880 --> 46:55.916
Well, there was a known rapist

46:55.949 --> 46:58.218
who appears to have
been in the area.

46:58.252 --> 46:59.621
An old jailbird
who lived nearby.

46:59.654 --> 47:02.256
And her classmate,
Emil Bachmann.

47:03.457 --> 47:05.359
That's what it said
in the paper.

47:05.392 --> 47:08.028
He was in custody
for a while, wasn't he?

47:08.062 --> 47:12.966
Arrested.
Dr. No let him go.

47:13.000 --> 47:18.105
Oh, you mean, um...
Neyman, the prosecutor?

47:18.138 --> 47:20.274
Neyman, yeah.

47:20.307 --> 47:23.077
Who actually had
a point for once.

47:24.378 --> 47:28.015
Mm, could I have
some more coffee?

47:28.048 --> 47:32.486
Three weeks later,
you arrested Jacob Kall.

47:32.520 --> 47:35.657
Talk about dragging your feet.

47:35.690 --> 47:39.993
You'd been informed that
he'd mistreated Vera for years.

47:40.027 --> 47:41.995
That was the only thing
that annoys me.

47:42.029 --> 47:45.432
Yeah, but three weeks?

47:45.466 --> 47:48.168
Is that what you call
good police work?

47:50.938 --> 47:56.477
Sometimes that's just how it is.

47:56.511 --> 47:59.213
But the worst of it was
that it gave him plenty of time

47:59.246 --> 48:00.981
to cover his tracks.

48:01.014 --> 48:02.550
And although he'd scrubbed
the place down,

48:02.584 --> 48:05.018
we quickly found
