<i>and if it wasn't in
the locker at school</i>

1:07:51.739 --> 1:07:54.842
<i>then it must be at her house.</i>

1:07:56.578 --> 1:07:59.413
<i>So, I had to go around
to see her parents,</i>

1:07:59.446 --> 1:08:02.282
<i>which is the absolute
last thing I wanted to do.</i>

1:08:02.316 --> 1:08:05.352
Even if,
God forbid she's dead,

1:08:05.385 --> 1:08:07.855
she still deserves a proper
school graduation report.

1:08:07.889 --> 1:08:09.591
Right.

1:08:09.624 --> 1:08:11.191
And it must be fair.

1:08:11.926 --> 1:08:13.360
Correct.

1:08:14.529 --> 1:08:16.129
Just because she's disappeared,

1:08:16.163 --> 1:08:19.466
doesn't mean you have to be
excessively generous.

1:08:19.499 --> 1:08:21.468
Just fair.

1:08:22.670 --> 1:08:24.404
I think you understand
what I mean.

1:08:31.779 --> 1:08:35.683
Erich Neumann-Hansen.
Headmaster, City College.

1:08:35.717 --> 1:08:36.851
Hello.

1:08:36.884 --> 1:08:38.753
Henry Maertens.
I'm the one who called.

1:08:38.786 --> 1:08:40.187
Yes.

1:08:42.924 --> 1:08:44.559
Might we come in?

1:08:44.592 --> 1:08:46.561
Oh, yes, please.

1:08:48.763 --> 1:08:50.798
Sorry about the food.

1:08:50.832 --> 1:08:52.767
We are the ones
who should apologize,

1:08:52.800 --> 1:08:55.302
barging in like this
during your lunch.

1:08:55.970 --> 1:08:58.740
But we have decided...

1:08:58.773 --> 1:09:03.511
that Vera must have her school
reports, despite all.

1:09:04.344 --> 1:09:06.179
We mustn't lose hope.

1:09:06.213 --> 1:09:07.615
I'd like to take a look
at a school essay

1:09:07.649 --> 1:09:09.684
that Vera was working on.

1:09:09.717 --> 1:09:11.519
I don't know if perhaps
you know where Vera keeps...

1:09:11.552 --> 1:09:13.554
Of course, we know.

1:09:14.956 --> 1:09:19.393
I assume you mean
her special report on Céline

1:09:20.695 --> 1:09:25.432
that was due to be
turned in Friday?

1:09:25.465 --> 1:09:29.236
<i>I was anything but
comfortable with the situation.</i>

1:09:29.269 --> 1:09:30.571
<i>Hated it.</i>

1:09:34.408 --> 1:09:36.878
- Top drawer.
- All right. Thanks.

1:09:47.789 --> 1:09:49.824
I don't want anything
removed from here.

1:09:49.857 --> 1:09:51.893
Yeah. Of course not.
Of course.

1:09:59.801 --> 1:10:01.636
Could I get a moment to myself?

1:10:09.944 --> 1:10:12.714
<i>At first, I found it
very hard to concentrate.</i>

1:10:12.747 --> 1:10:14.381
<i>That was largely because
I could...</i>

1:10:14.414 --> 1:10:17.752
<i>I could feel
the presence of her father.</i>

1:10:17.785 --> 1:10:20.253
<i>His eyes just, like,
drilling into my back.</i>

1:10:20.287 --> 1:10:22.523
<i>Even though he wasn't
really in the room.</i>

1:10:22.557 --> 1:10:24.224
<i>But I could feel him.</i>

1:10:26.994 --> 1:10:29.329
<i>And then I got drawn into
what she'd written.</i>

1:10:29.362 --> 1:10:30.531
<i>She's very good.</i>

1:10:30.565 --> 1:10:32.867
<i>She'd largely finished
the work.</i>

1:10:34.569 --> 1:10:36.537
<i>And when I got home
I regretted the visit.</i>

1:10:36.571 --> 1:10:39.406
<i>It just felt like
we'd encroached</i>

1:10:39.439 --> 1:10:42.610
<i>or had butted into
their sorrow.</i>

1:10:42.643 --> 1:10:44.011
<i>What did it really matter,</i>

1:10:44.045 --> 1:10:47.615
<i>you know, what final grade
Vera received?</i>

1:10:47.648 --> 1:10:49.717
Sorry for disturbing.

1:10:49.751 --> 1:10:51.284
Have you seen Tomas?

1:10:51.318 --> 1:10:52.920
Oh.

1:10:55.022 --> 1:10:58.993
Yes, yes, yes.

1:10:59.961 --> 1:11:01.696
Yes, come on.

1:11:01.729 --> 1:11:03.598
<i>Come on.</i>

1:11:03.631 --> 1:11:05.967
Two days later,
Jacob Kall was arrested.

1:11:07.434 --> 1:11:09.637
How did that feel?

1:11:09.670 --> 1:11:12.540
- Surreal.
- In what sense?

1:11:12.573 --> 1:11:15.042
In the sense that we'd been
allowed to walk around the kitchen

1:11:15.076 --> 1:11:18.079
where Vera had been
beaten to death by her father.

1:11:50.745 --> 1:11:54.081
Look... Samaria.

1:11:54.816 --> 1:11:56.349
It's for sale.

1:12:00.087 --> 1:12:03.024
Did you bring your camera?

1:12:03.057 --> 1:12:05.492
Oh, the house
isn't going anywhere.

1:12:07.427 --> 1:12:09.697
Feels very strange
coming back here.

1:12:09.730 --> 1:12:12.399
Really, what I
what I was thinking.

1:12:12.432 --> 1:12:15.670
She's buried somewhere
under your feet.

1:12:17.470 --> 1:12:19.006
Welcome.

1:12:20.575 --> 1:12:22.777
I must apologize
for the state of things here,

1:12:22.810 --> 1:12:26.113
but the place is sold as seen.

1:12:26.147 --> 1:12:28.516
Perfect environment
for children to grow up in.

1:12:28.549 --> 1:12:33.921
Great potential for conversion, renovation...

1:12:33.955 --> 1:12:36.791
Or rip it down,
build your own.

1:12:38.025 --> 1:12:39.861
Why don't you
have a look around?

1:12:40.194 --> 1:12:41.562
Thanks.

1:12:46.200 --> 1:12:48.135
Contents included.

1:13:14.695 --> 1:13:16.998
It's exactly
like I remember it.

1:13:30.211 --> 1:13:31.612
Pieter Vogel.

1:13:31.646 --> 1:13:33.648
What?

1:13:33.681 --> 1:13:37.084
I'm just thinking maybe
she had a thing with Pieter Vogel.

1:13:37.118 --> 1:13:40.655
Really? Have you
spoken to him about it?

1:13:40.688 --> 1:13:45.126
No, he would never have been able
to keep his mouth shut.

1:13:45.159 --> 1:13:46.694
Oh.

1:14:01.042 --> 1:14:02.610
One thing's for certain, anyway,

1:14:02.643 --> 1:14:05.146
Pieter never slept in this bed,
because if he had,

1:14:05.179 --> 1:14:07.848
Jacob Kall would've
knocked him off as well.

1:14:12.853 --> 1:14:14.722
Mm.

1:14:14.755 --> 1:14:16.624
Why don't you
have a look around?

1:14:16.657 --> 1:14:19.727
So, when did you meet Clara?

1:14:21.062 --> 1:14:22.930
Clara? Why do ask?

1:14:22.964 --> 1:14:25.199
Just curious.

1:14:26.701 --> 1:14:28.669
We met a year...

1:14:28.703 --> 1:14:31.005
a year or two
after this in Antwerp.

1:14:33.074 --> 1:14:36.277
What about when you were
living here in Kaalbringen?

1:14:36.310 --> 1:14:41.882
- What?
- Well, did you have some special lady friend?

1:14:41.916 --> 1:14:44.752
No. No, that wasn't, um...

1:14:44.785 --> 1:14:47.555
It wasn't in the script,
so to speak.

1:14:47.588 --> 1:14:50.257
- <i>Groundhog Day.</i>
- Exactly.

1:14:51.826 --> 1:14:53.794
Well, I know a couple
of the girls from our class

1:14:53.828 --> 1:14:55.696
who were more than interested.

1:14:56.931 --> 1:14:59.767
- Taboo.
- What did you say?

1:15:00.568 --> 1:15:02.303
Never on the cards.

1:15:04.905 --> 1:15:07.742
<i>I don't think I found Henry</i>

1:15:07.775 --> 1:15:09.176
<i>incredibly attractive.</i>

1:15:10.811 --> 1:15:16.217
<i>Um, he was so sweet
and, sort of, cute.</i>

1:15:16.250 --> 1:15:19.186
<i>And if you made
a special effort</i>

1:15:19.220 --> 1:15:21.322
<i>and seemed a bit interested
he blushed.</i>

1:15:21.355 --> 1:15:24.925
<i>So, without Henry Maertens,</i>

1:15:24.959 --> 1:15:28.562
<i>that last term
would have been bloody boring.</i>

1:15:28.596 --> 1:15:32.133
<i>Yeah, so, all the girls
had a crush on Henry Maertens?</i>

1:15:32.166 --> 1:15:34.235
- <i>Mm-hm.</i>
- <i>What about the boys?</i>

1:15:34.268 --> 1:15:37.238
- <i>Who did they love?</i>
- <i>You know...</i>

1:15:37.271 --> 1:15:38.973
<i>Yes, but you say it.</i>

1:15:39.006 --> 1:15:43.077
<i>Vera, of course.</i>

1:15:43.110 --> 1:15:49.083
<i>I think out of everyone
you really knew her the best.</i>

1:15:49.116 --> 1:15:51.585
<i>Yeah. Vera was...</i>

1:15:51.619 --> 1:15:55.056
<i>the finest, the best,</i>

1:15:55.089 --> 1:16:01.195
<i>and I still miss her,
so terribly still,</i>

1:16:01.228 --> 1:16:05.766
<i>and I think I told her everything.</i>

1:16:05.800 --> 1:16:10.905
<i>She was always so wise
and thoughtful,</i>

1:16:10.938 --> 1:16:13.874
<i>as if she knew everything.</i>

1:16:16.110 --> 1:16:21.215
<i>Did she ever tell you
anything about herself, her life?</i>

1:16:21.248 --> 1:16:24.085
<i>Oh, no. She didn't.</i>

1:16:24.819 --> 1:16:26.654
<i>Hardly anything.</i>

1:16:27.288 --> 1:16:29.023
<i>Some things.</i>

1:16:30.224 --> 1:16:32.693
<i>I know she had
a tough time at home...</i>

1:16:32.726 --> 1:16:35.096
<i>I saw her bruises.</i>

1:16:35.129 --> 1:16:38.199
<i>She... she tried
covering them up with makeup.</i>

1:16:38.232 --> 1:16:41.368
Hi. Yes, yeah.
I... I have it right here.

1:16:41.402 --> 1:16:43.637
That's... that's why
I tried to call you earlier.

1:16:43.671 --> 1:16:45.973
Um... Ah, no, it's in the car.

1:16:46.006 --> 1:16:48.876
<i>Never talked about it
ever, she didn't want pity.</i>

1:16:48.909 --> 1:16:51.011
<i>Do you think maybe she was gay?</i>

1:16:51.045 --> 1:16:54.248
- <i>What?</i>
- <i>Well, just, you know, that...</i>

1:16:54.281 --> 1:16:56.150
<i>As you said,
all the boys were interested,</i>

1:16:56.183 --> 1:16:58.652
<i>but she was just really didn't
seem to care about at all.</i>

1:16:58.686 --> 1:17:00.287
<i>It's not
so very surprising, you know.</i>

1:17:00.321 --> 1:17:01.922
<i>Vera was smart.</i>

1:17:01.956 --> 1:17:04.959
<i>And she just wanted
school to be over</i>

1:17:04.992 --> 1:17:06.994
<i>so she could start living.</i>

1:17:07.027 --> 1:17:09.396
<i>She longed to get away
from her family.</i>

1:17:09.430 --> 1:17:10.965
<i>No wonder.</i>

1:17:10.998 --> 1:17:14.068
<i>And did she...</i>

1:17:14.101 --> 1:17:15.302
<i>Did she have a boyfriend?</i>

1:17:15.336 --> 1:17:16.737
<i>Not that I know of.</i>

1:17:17.905 --> 1:17:22.243
<i>Maybe Maertens, if so.</i>

1:17:22.910 --> 1:17:24.778
<i>Henry Maertens?</i>

1:17:24.812 --> 1:17:27.882
<i>Yeah.
But she never told me anything.</i>

1:17:29.316 --> 1:17:31.852
Yeah.

1:17:34.755 --> 1:17:37.725
Great. Yeah. I'll...
I'll speak to you.

1:17:37.758 --> 1:17:40.861
<i>But if you'll ask me,
I'd say Henry.</i>

1:17:45.132 --> 1:17:47.301
When did you
meet with Claire Meitens?

1:17:49.770 --> 1:17:51.438
Before you and I met in Maardam.

1:17:57.912 --> 1:17:59.980
And when were you
gonna tell me that?

1:18:01.315 --> 1:18:04.952
- Well... I...
- Or...

1:18:04.985 --> 1:18:06.320
You know, I don't know
what to think, Henry,

1:18:06.353 --> 1:18:07.888
because I know
that you haven't been honest,

1:18:07.922 --> 1:18:09.857
- and I know that you've lied.
- Lied?!

1:18:09.890 --> 1:18:12.826
Lied, Paula?!
You're the one who's lied!

1:18:12.860 --> 1:18:15.129
- Yes, okay!
- Yeah, do you know what I think this is?!

1:18:15.162 --> 1:18:18.165
This is jealousy!
That's what this bloody film is!

1:18:18.199 --> 1:18:21.101
Your jealousy and the fact that
Vera wasn't in love with you.

1:18:21.135 --> 1:18:23.804
- Okay, that's not true.
- 'Cause that's what this whole bloody film is, isn't it?

1:18:23.837 --> 1:18:28.409
It's not actually about Vera,
it's about your gigantic narcissistic ego.

1:18:38.852 --> 1:18:41.188
Yeah, I was in love with her.

1:18:42.790 --> 1:18:45.192
But I accepted
that it wasn't mutual.

1:18:45.226 --> 1:18:47.061
You see, I knew it.

1:18:47.094 --> 1:18:49.430
You've got a fucking weird way of
working, you know that?

1:18:49.463 --> 1:18:51.365
I mean,
you and your twisted theories.

1:18:51.398 --> 1:18:53.400
And whether something
is true or not,

1:18:53.434 --> 1:18:55.402
it just seems to be
fucking irrelevant to you.

1:18:55.436 --> 1:18:59.940
Yeah, well, if it's not true, Henry,
then why don't you explain this?

1:19:09.483 --> 1:19:14.755
"Be thou the rainbow
and the storms of life. -H"

1:19:15.189 --> 1:19:16.991
For Henry?

1:19:18.859 --> 1:19:20.327
Where did you get this?

1:19:22.129 --> 1:19:25.032
I found it in Samaria
about a month ago.

1:19:29.436 --> 1:19:32.540
- You don't know shit.
- And you do?

1:19:38.345 --> 1:19:43.017
I loved Vera...
and she loved me.

1:19:52.860 --> 1:19:54.461
No camera.

1:19:56.263 --> 1:19:57.532
No camera.

1:20:02.570 --> 1:20:04.539
Just give me some time.

1:20:17.051 --> 1:20:19.521
There's a darkness to it
and a sense of foreboding to it.

1:20:19.554 --> 1:20:22.323
But there really
is a sense of passion.

1:20:22.356 --> 1:20:23.625
There really is
a sense of passion,

1:20:23.658 --> 1:20:25.092
but let me ask you
this one question:

1:20:25.125 --> 1:20:26.528
Do you not think
there is a pessimism

1:20:26.561 --> 1:20:27.961
to the whole thing,
do you not think that there is

1:20:27.995 --> 1:20:29.263
death on every single page?

1:20:29.296 --> 1:20:31.899
I would say
exactly the opposite.

1:20:31.932 --> 1:20:36.270
I think the language is so full of
life and so incredibly beautiful.

1:20:36.303 --> 1:20:39.006
I would like to write about
Céline's use of language instead.

1:20:39.039 --> 1:20:41.875
<i>I set aside about 30
minutes, I think,</i>

1:20:41.909 --> 1:20:44.244
<i>but we must have sat there
for about two hours.</i>

1:20:44.278 --> 1:20:47.649
<i>I would never normally have devoted
so much time to just one student,</i>

1:20:47.682 --> 1:20:52.319
<i>but, uh...
I didn't want to leave,</i>

1:20:54.955 --> 1:20:56.256
And I liked her being there.

1:20:56.290 --> 1:20:59.460
I liked...

1:20:59.493 --> 1:21:06.568
I liked her laugh,
and her thoughts, and her...

1:21:09.370 --> 1:21:13.407
Her everything, I suppose.

1:21:13.440 --> 1:21:17.010
We agreed to meet again the
very next afternoon, I remember.

1:21:17.044 --> 1:21:21.348
Under the pretext of Vera wanted
to talk about her idea of...

1:21:21.382 --> 1:21:24.218
of Céline's use of language,
but we both knew that wasn't the reason.

1:21:24.251 --> 1:21:28.255
I mean, we... we made up
various different excuses

1:21:28.288 --> 1:21:29.990
along the way
just to be together.

1:21:30.023 --> 1:21:31.559
It's getting a bit cold.
I'm gonna run in

1:21:31.593 --> 1:21:33.494
and get a jumper, okay?
Do you... do you want one?

1:21:33.528 --> 1:21:35.162
No, thanks.

1:21:49.977 --> 1:21:51.646
The library obviously

1:21:51.679 --> 1:21:54.982
<i>had its fixed opening hours...</i>

1:21:57.384 --> 1:21:59.186
<i>but I had a key.</i>

1:22:01.288 --> 1:22:02.557
<i>So, we knew we wouldn't
be disturbed,</i>

1:22:02.590 --> 1:22:04.391
<i>well, at least
for a little while.</i>

1:22:55.142 --> 1:22:57.177
<i>You must've had
a fuck load of luck.</i>

1:22:57.211 --> 1:22:59.079
<i>Well, then, maybe.</i>

1:22:59.112 --> 1:23:01.583
What would've happened
if someone had found out?

1:23:01.616 --> 1:23:03.417
Honestly speaking,
I don't know.

1:23:03.450 --> 1:23:04.786
I mean, it's out of the
question, of course,

1:23:04.819 --> 1:23:06.621
it was taboo, like I said.

1:23:06.654 --> 1:23:10.525
But also... beautiful.

1:23:12.392 --> 1:23:13.460
Hm...

1:23:16.196 --> 1:23:20.234
The following week I, uh,
smuggled her back to Mrs. Kuntze's house.

1:23:20.267 --> 1:23:22.436
I think Vera told her parents...

1:23:24.171 --> 1:23:25.540
<i>she was staying on the library</i>

1:23:25.573 --> 1:23:27.742
<i>or something
for an extra few hours.</i>

1:23:33.781 --> 1:23:36.283
<i>Maybe it's a bit exaggerated
to say that I smuggled her in.</i>

1:23:36.316 --> 1:23:40.053
<i>I'm sure, Mrs. Kuntze would've
been very accommodating.</i>

1:23:40.087 --> 1:23:42.690
- Meow.
- Shh.

1:23:42.724 --> 1:23:45.292
<i>We just...
we just had to be very careful.</i>

1:23:46.594 --> 1:23:48.763
It's just one, one bit...

1:23:48.796 --> 1:23:50.297
that I have to
talk to you about.

1:23:50.330 --> 1:23:52.199
<i>Vera absolutely did not want</i>

1:23:52.232 --> 1:23:53.735
<i>her parents to find out that...</i>

1:23:53.768 --> 1:23:55.369
- It's one bit.
- I can wait.

1:23:55.402 --> 1:23:58.272
<i>It wasn't even an option
and I understood it.</i>

1:23:59.607 --> 1:24:02.677
<i>I'd seen the marks on her...
on her body,</i>

1:24:02.710 --> 1:24:05.713
<i>not... not that she
talked about it.</i>

1:24:05.747 --> 1:24:07.447
<i>Maybe it was then
that I realized</i>

1:24:07.481 --> 1:24:09.216
<i>that I was actually
exposing her to a risk.</i>

1:24:09.249 --> 1:24:11.686
And now you're in trouble,
I'd say.

1:24:19.594 --> 1:24:21.829
And when I was alone,

1:24:21.863 --> 1:24:27.569
and all of this initial rush
had... had settled...

1:24:27.602 --> 1:24:31.171
I knew that our relationship
just could never work.

1:24:31.204 --> 1:24:33.140
What about at the party, then?

1:24:33.173 --> 1:24:37.210
On the last night,
did you not see each other?

1:24:37.244 --> 1:24:38.646
<i>But of course,
from time to time,</i>

1:24:38.680 --> 1:24:39.781
<i>you might just
find yourself needing</i>

1:24:39.814 --> 1:24:41.248
<i>a bit of actual guidance</i>

1:24:41.281 --> 1:24:42.884
from your
highly salaried lecturer.

1:24:42.917 --> 1:24:46.320
And as you look up
eagerly seeking his attention,

1:24:46.353 --> 1:24:49.757
you are met with the sight of your
eminently qualified tutor, Wasserman,

1:24:49.791 --> 1:24:52.694
sitting bolt upright
in his opulent chair

1:24:52.727 --> 1:24:56.229
behind his imposing desk,
taking a nap...

1:24:57.331 --> 1:24:59.601
It's not true.
It's all a lie.

1:24:59.634 --> 1:25:01.869
How does he defy the laws of physics?

1:25:01.903 --> 1:25:05.172
We were able to internalize
this extraordinary feat

1:25:05.205 --> 1:25:07.642
of vertical hibernation with
the help of your Jovan's mobile.

1:25:07.675 --> 1:25:11.546
And, as you know, it was published
eventually in the college magazine.

1:25:11.579 --> 1:25:12.914
<i>Even though
it was very dangerous</i>

1:25:12.947 --> 1:25:15.482
<i>for Vera and I
to see each other,</i>

1:25:15.516 --> 1:25:19.419
<i>my body just ached for her.</i>

1:25:19.453 --> 1:25:21.556
Our only element of
regret, looking back on it,

1:25:21.589 --> 1:25:25.258
is that we didn't manage to record
the accompanying sound effects.

1:25:25.292 --> 1:25:28.228
Good night, kids.
Don't do anything I wouldn't do.

1:25:28.261 --> 1:25:29.631
- Good night.
- Don't go, Henry.

1:25:29.664 --> 1:25:31.164
Dance with me.

1:25:31.198 --> 1:25:32.767
All right.
Good night, good night.

1:25:32.800 --> 1:25:34.334
I have to go, I have to go,
I have to go. All right.

1:25:34.368 --> 1:25:35.603
Don't be such a boring old fart.

1:25:35.637 --> 1:25:37.270
Okay. Good night.

1:25:37.304 --> 1:25:39.239
<i>Emil Bachman,
I think had stumbled home,</i>

1:25:39.272 --> 1:25:42.376
<i>and then I went down
to our usual meeting place.</i>

1:25:43.511 --> 1:25:45.747
<i>Far too early,
as it turned out.</i>

1:25:45.780 --> 1:25:48.750
<i>I thought it'd take 15 minutes
to get onto the bridge.</i>

1:25:48.783 --> 1:25:53.153
<i>I must have walked very quickly because it
wouldn't have taken me more than five, I think.</i>

1:25:54.722 --> 1:25:56.824
<i>And so many thoughts
were passing through my head</i>

1:25:56.858 --> 1:25:58.526
<i>as I waited and I remembered...</i>

1:25:59.894 --> 1:26:01.395
<i>Has she snuck at home</i>

1:26:01.428 --> 1:26:03.831
<i>or has she stayed behind
at the party?</i>

1:26:04.832 --> 1:26:06.534
<i>I didn't know what to think.</i>

1:26:08.268 --> 1:26:11.371
But then she arrived,
slightly out of breath,

1:26:11.405 --> 1:26:12.874
on her bicycle.

1:26:15.308 --> 1:26:18.245
And then we went back
to the Pampas, to my place.

1:26:26.888 --> 1:26:29.624
You're right, it is...
it is getting cold, isn't it?

1:26:29.657 --> 1:26:32.694
And then you went back
to Mrs. Kuntze's.

1:26:34.494 --> 1:26:36.798
She never went home,
is that what you're saying?

1:26:36.831 --> 1:26:38.666
I'm gonna go get a...
a sweater.

1:26:38.700 --> 1:26:40.768
- Well, I'll get it.
- Coming right back.

1:27:05.793 --> 1:27:09.329
Henry, I can...
I can explain.

1:27:20.908 --> 1:27:22.777
Stop.

1:27:22.810 --> 1:27:24.712
Stop, stop! I can...

1:27:35.690 --> 1:27:37.024
Come back!

1:27:38.559 --> 1:27:41.896
No! Stop! No!

1:27:44.532 --> 1:27:46.901
What the fuck are you doing?

1:27:49.937 --> 1:27:52.774
You're a sick person,
you know that.

1:27:52.807 --> 1:27:55.076
No, please...
Oh...

1:27:55.109 --> 1:27:56.811
No.

1:27:56.844 --> 1:27:59.614
No. Oh, no.

1:29:53.928 --> 1:29:55.930
- Are you awake, darling?
- Yeah.

1:29:56.864 --> 1:29:58.165
I have to go.

1:30:01.869 --> 1:30:03.704
We should talk, Vera.

1:30:03.738 --> 1:30:05.706
We're always talking.

1:30:10.477 --> 1:30:11.712
I don't think what we're...

1:30:11.746 --> 1:30:13.446
I don't think
what we're doing is right

1:30:13.480 --> 1:30:16.117
at this point in time.

1:30:16.150 --> 1:30:17.818
I'm sorry.

1:30:18.786 --> 1:30:20.087
What?

1:30:21.689 --> 1:30:24.659
I think we should maybe
take a break, you and I.

1:30:35.136 --> 1:30:37.972
The thing is, Vera,

1:30:38.005 --> 1:30:42.043
you never tell me anything...
ever.

1:30:43.644 --> 1:30:48.182
And I... I do see what's
happening, I do understand.

1:30:59.860 --> 1:31:01.228
I know this man is your father,

1:31:01.262 --> 1:31:03.864
but you have got to
report him to the police.

1:31:07.601 --> 1:31:10.071
I'm saying this
for your best interest...

1:31:10.104 --> 1:31:11.872
And that would be to not
be there for me?

1:31:11.906 --> 1:31:15.176
- Of course not.
- How soothing.

1:31:15.209 --> 1:31:17.211
You can't continue like this.

1:31:20.047 --> 1:31:22.850
Vera, Vera.

1:31:22.883 --> 1:31:24.585
<i>Wait, Vera.</i>

1:31:26.620 --> 1:31:31.092
Suspected assault,
damage to property,

1:31:31.125 --> 1:31:33.961
but you are also wanted
for questioning...

1:31:35.196 --> 1:31:38.966
for withholding information

1:31:39.000 --> 1:31:43.838
into the investigation
of the murder of Vera Kall.

1:31:43.871 --> 1:31:46.240
In other words, Vera Kall

1:31:46.273 --> 1:31:49.243
did not cycle home at midnight

1:31:49.276 --> 1:31:53.647
but three hours later.

1:31:53.681 --> 1:31:56.317
Now, although you were
well aware

1:31:56.350 --> 1:32:00.187
that the police investigation
into her disappearance

1:32:00.221 --> 1:32:03.090
was not making any progress,

1:32:03.124 --> 1:32:06.327
you chose not to
tell us what you knew.

1:32:06.360 --> 1:32:09.597
I thought she'd ran away.
I thought she was staying away on purpose.

1:32:11.098 --> 1:32:15.669
I thought she'd get in touch...
once things had calmed down.

1:32:15.703 --> 1:32:17.705
Or you're lying

1:32:17.738 --> 1:32:20.174
and we've got the wrong bloke
locked up in prison.

1:32:20.207 --> 1:32:21.876
I did not kill Vera, all right.
I would never...

1:32:21.909 --> 1:32:26.113
All right, then. I don't happen
to think that either.

1:32:28.883 --> 1:32:30.151
I loved her.

1:32:30.184 --> 1:32:32.853
Hmm. But apparently,

1:32:32.887 --> 1:32:35.923
not enough to share with us
what you knew.

1:32:35.956 --> 1:32:38.292
Well, that was the last thing she
would have wanted, for God's sake.

1:32:38.325 --> 1:32:40.094
She was terrified of her father.

1:32:40.127 --> 1:32:43.864
If we had known then
what we know now

1:32:43.898 --> 1:32:48.803
we probably would have arrested
Jacob Kall a few weeks earlier.

1:32:48.836 --> 1:32:51.305
We might have found the remains,

1:32:51.338 --> 1:32:56.343
or at best,
found her still alive.

1:33:04.718 --> 1:33:06.353
<i>He was hitting her.</i>

1:33:06.387 --> 1:33:10.357
<i>I saw the bruises on her body,
if he had found out...</i>

1:33:10.391 --> 1:33:12.893
<i>I didn't want her
to put her through that risk.</i>

1:33:12.927 --> 1:33:14.695
<i>How many times
do I have to tell you?</i>

1:33:14.728 --> 1:33:17.998
<i>Well, either that, or you were
just too much of a coward</i>

1:33:18.032 --> 1:33:19.633
<i>to own up to what you had done.</i>

1:33:19.667 --> 1:33:21.235
- <i>No.</i>
- <i>I mean, a teacher</i>

1:33:21.268 --> 1:33:23.204
<i>seducing a student.</i>

1:33:23.237 --> 1:33:27.241
Maybe not illegal
but inappropriate.

1:33:28.909 --> 1:33:33.080
In no way are you being dropped
from this investigation,

1:33:33.114 --> 1:33:36.684
but we're not gonna
hold onto you any longer.

1:33:36.717 --> 1:33:39.720
As for the assault,
you can expect a...

1:33:39.753 --> 1:33:43.657
a fine
and a conditional sentence.

1:35:27.328 --> 1:35:29.330
Should I call the police?

1:35:31.365 --> 1:35:33.467
That's ten thousand Euros.
It should be enough to cover

1:35:33.501 --> 1:35:35.402
the cost of your equipment,
at least.

1:35:36.303 --> 1:35:38.072
Move.

1:35:42.209 --> 1:35:43.377
Are you coming?

1:35:45.446 --> 1:35:46.880
<i>All her things were gone</i>

1:35:46.914 --> 1:35:48.782
by the time
I got back to Antwerp.

1:35:49.483 --> 1:35:51.285
Was she answering her phone?

1:35:52.119 --> 1:35:53.921
What did she say?

1:35:55.856 --> 1:35:58.325
What? Nothing endearing, then.

1:36:00.261 --> 1:36:01.929
I miss Clara.

1:36:04.398 --> 1:36:06.900
I miss my dog.

1:36:07.868 --> 1:36:11.539
Yeah.
You've paid a high price.

1:36:13.274 --> 1:36:15.209
Me too, in a way.

1:36:18.178 --> 1:36:20.481
Obviously, I shouldn't have
done what I did either.

1:36:22.149 --> 1:36:24.918
Definitely crossed the line.

1:36:26.954 --> 1:36:28.155
It's really made me think,

1:36:28.188 --> 1:36:30.491
I mean, your reaction
was totally justified

1:36:30.525 --> 1:36:33.294
and I should prob... No, I should...
I should apologize.

1:36:33.327 --> 1:36:35.829
No, it's wrong.

1:36:35.863 --> 1:36:38.332
I'm the one who's at fault,
and if I had just told the truth

1:36:38.365 --> 1:36:40.968
when all this happened
all those years ago, and then...

1:36:41.001 --> 1:36:45.573
Then I'd never have
anything to hide from you.

1:36:45.607 --> 1:36:49.243
Instead, I've just chosen to
keep a secret all these years.

1:36:51.378 --> 1:36:53.080
I loved Vera.

1:36:56.551 --> 1:37:01.055
My God, you must have
hated Jacob Kall.

1:37:01.088 --> 1:37:02.423
Probably still hate him.

1:37:02.456 --> 1:37:06.193
Yeah. Yeah, I do.

1:37:08.462 --> 1:37:11.365
I hate him with
every bit of my heart.

1:37:16.136 --> 1:37:17.539
I've dropped the project.

1:37:18.405 --> 1:37:20.341
It's not gonna be a film.

1:37:22.910 --> 1:37:23.877
Good.

1:37:23.911 --> 1:37:26.280
It's just too, uh...

1:37:26.313 --> 1:37:27.615
Too heavy.

1:37:32.119 --> 1:37:33.521
Sad.

1:37:37.057 --> 1:37:38.425
Too private.

1:37:41.962 --> 1:37:46.200
Sometimes it is just better to
let things lie, like you said.

1:37:48.102 --> 1:37:49.571
And, uh...

1:37:50.605 --> 1:37:53.307
and maybe I just have to accept

1:37:53.340 --> 1:37:58.245
that she lies buried somewhere,

1:37:58.278 --> 1:38:00.381
the forest's edge,

1:38:00.414 --> 1:38:04.385
and that the memory of Vera
is more important.

1:38:07.187 --> 1:38:10.357
Sometimes I like to pretend
that the drunk at the station...

1:38:11.291 --> 1:38:13.927
- did actually see her.
- Mm.

1:38:13.961 --> 1:38:16.463
That she'd reached
an end point that morning and...

1:38:16.497 --> 1:38:18.666
<i>managed to get away.</i>

1:38:19.734 --> 1:38:22.970
<i>That in spite of everything,</i>

1:38:23.003 --> 1:38:27.609
<i>she actually boarded
the first train to Altmaar,</i>

1:38:27.642 --> 1:38:32.312
<i>while the rest of us were
lying there, sleeping it off,</i>

1:38:32.346 --> 1:38:37.084
<i>she packed her bag
and left Samaria for good.</i>

1:38:39.286 --> 1:38:42.724
<i>Perhaps without even knowing
where she was going.</i>

1:38:42.757 --> 1:38:45.593
<i>And for the first time
she felt free.</i>

1:38:48.395 --> 1:38:50.698
<i>Really free.</i>

1:38:52.466 --> 1:38:56.303
<i>I think she found a better life
somewhere else;</i>

1:38:58.038 --> 1:39:01.543
<i>another town,
another country...</i>

1:39:02.644 --> 1:39:05.613
<i>because she was
worth that much.</i>

1:39:06.781 --> 1:39:09.551
<i>Vera deserved
the best of everything.</i>

1:39:56.497 --> 1:39:58.633
- Who's that?
- No idea.

1:39:58.666 --> 1:40:00.133
I said her name was Clara,

1:40:00.167 --> 1:40:02.369
and she works in
our Brussels office

1:40:02.402 --> 1:40:03.671
unless I'm mistaken.

1:40:04.672 --> 1:40:07.341
- Thank you.
- Thank you.
